cs.MA, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is likely because the paper proposes a mobile crowdsensing approach, which involves multiple agents (smartphones) working together to identify POI. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely because the paper discusses identifying common POI among users of a given indoor environment, which involves analyzing social networks of users. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a possible category because the paper relies on Wi-Fi access points to accurately identify user POI. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category because the paper proposes a smartphone application based system architecture to scan the surrounding Wi-Fi AP and measure the cosine similarity of received signal strengths. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a possible category because the paper discusses a smartphone application that users interact with to identify POI, and the results of the study could have implications for improving user experience in indoor environments.
